{"lemma":"آلِيِّي","slug":"آلِيِّي","root":"#.#.ل","root_slug":"_-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-_-ل","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"آلِيّ","root":"","pos":"P","occurrence_count":742},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1131","n1146","n1147","n1133","n1139","n1140","n1141","n1142","n1143","n1145","n1154"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to promise"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take an oath"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔaː.laː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1131","headword_ar":"اـِلَى","root":"Alw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Sb, is originally with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of the ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the final] alif; and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for the alifs [in these two particles] are not susceptible of imáleh; [i. e., they may not be pronounced ilè and 'alè;] and if either be used as the proper name of a man, the dual [of the former] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilawaAni","text_ar":"اـِلَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [that of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalawaAni","text_ar":"عَلَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but when a pronoun is affixed to it, the alif is changed into yé, so that you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though some of the Arabs leave it as it was, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaAka","text_ar":"اـِلَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAka","text_ar":"عَلَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) It is a prep., or particle governing a noun in the gen. case, (S, Mughnee, K,) and denotes the end, as opposed to ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which denotes] the beginning, of an extent, or of the space between two points or limits; (S, M;) or the end of an extent (T, Mughnee, K) of place; [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as far as;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as in the phrase [in the Kur xvii. 1],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Almasojidi AlHaraAmi A_ilaY Almasojidi AlA^aqoSaY","text_ar":"مِنَ المَسْجِدِ الحَرَامِ اـِلَى المَسْجِدِ الاَقْصَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From the Sacred Mosque to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as far as, the Furthest Mosque;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning from the mosque of Mekkeh to that of Jerusalem]; (Mughnee, K;) or in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarajotu mina Alkuwfapi A_ilaY mak~apa","text_ar":"خَرَجْتُ مِنَ الكُوفَةِ اـِلَى مَكَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I went forth from El-Koofeh to Mekkeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"], which may mean that you entered it, [namely, the latter place,] or that you reached it without entering it, for the end includes the beginning of the limit and the furthest part thereof, but does not extend beyond it. (S.) [In some respects it agrees with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY","text_ar":"حَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. And sometimes it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Towards;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naZara A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"نَظَرَ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked towards me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAla A_ilayohi","text_ar":"مَالَ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, inclined towards him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  It also denotes the end of a space of time; [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To, till,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as in the saying [in the Kur ii. 183],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a A^atim~uwA AlS~iyaAma A_ilaY All~ayoli","text_ar":"ثُمَّ اَتِمُّوا الصِّيَامَ اـِلَى اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then complets ye the fasting to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"till,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until, the night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee, K.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY A^ano","text_ar":"اـِلَى اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(followed by a mansoob aor.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Till,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY mataY","text_ar":"اـِلَى مَتَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Till,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until, what time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when?"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how long?"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, till,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until, the time when."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also the last sentence in this paragraph.] ―         -b3-  [In like manner it is used in the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY gayori *lika","text_ar":"اـِلَى غَيْرِ ذلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY A=xirihi","text_ar":"اـِلَى ا=خِرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, ("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And so on,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to other things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the end thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"equivalent to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"et cœtera."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  Sometimes, (S,) it occurs in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa","text_ar":"مَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mughnee, K,) when a thing is joined to another thing; (Mughnee, K;) as in the phrase [in the Kur iii. 45 and lxi. 14],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^anoSaAriY A_ilaY All~`hi","text_ar":"مَنْ اَنْصَارِى اـِلَى اللّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who will be my aiders with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in addition to, God?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, Mughnee, K,) accord. to the Koofees and some of the Basrees; (Mughnee;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who will be joined to God in aiding me?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) and as in the saying [in the Kur iv. 2],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA taA^okuluwA","text_ar":"وَلَا تَاْكُلُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amowaAlahumo A_ilaY A^amowaAlikumo","text_ar":"اَمْوَالَهُمْ اـِلَى اَمْوَالِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And devour not ye their possessions with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in addition to, your possessions"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S;) and [in the same, ii. 13,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_i*aA xalawoA A_ilaY","text_ar":"وَاـِذَا خَلَوْا اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayaA Tiynihimo","text_ar":"شَيَا طِينِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when they are alone with their devils"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) and in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~awodu A_ilaY Al*~awodi A_ibilN","text_ar":"الذَّوْدُ اـِلَى الذَّوْدِ اـِبِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A few she-camels with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"added to, a few she-camels are a herd of camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, Mughnee, K,) a prov., meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little with a little makes much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*wd","text_ar":"ذود"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.;) though one may not say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY zayodK maAlN","text_ar":"اـِلَى زَيْدٍ مَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa zayodK maAlN","text_ar":"مَعَ زَيْدٍ مَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mughnee:) so too in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN HaliymN A_ilaY A^adabK wafiqohK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَلِيمٌ اـِلَى اَدَبٍ وَفِقْهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is clement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbearing, with good education,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"polite accomplishments, and intelligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the law"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, TA;) and so, accord. to Kh, in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomadu All~`ha A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اَحْمَدُ اللّٰهَ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I praise God with thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but see another rendering of this phrase below]. (ISh.) In the saying in the Kur [v. 8],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAgosiluwA wujuwhakumo waA^ayodiyakumo","text_ar":"فَاغْسِلُوا وُجُوهَكُمْ وَاَيْدِيَكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY AlmaraAfiqi","text_ar":"اـِلَى المَرَافِقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is disputed whether [the meaning be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then wash ye your faces, and your arms with the elbows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and your arms as far as the elbows;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., whether] the elbows be meant to be included among the parts to be washed, or excluded therefrom. (T.) A context sometimes shows that what follows it is included in what precedes it; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^otu AlquroA=na mino A^aw~alihi A_ilaY A=xirihi","text_ar":"قَرَاْتُ القُرْا=نَ مِنْ اَوَّلِهِ اـِلَى ا=خِرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recited, the Kurán, from the beginning thereof to the end thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or that it is excluded; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a A^atim~uwA AlS~iyaAma A_ilaY All~ayoli","text_ar":"ثُمَّ اَتِمُّوا الصِّيَامَ اـِلَى اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained above]: when this is not the case, some say that it is included if it be of the same kind [as that which precedes]; some, that it is included absolutely; and some, that it is excluded absolutely; and this is the right assertion; for with the context it is in most instances excluded. (Mughnee.) ―         -b5-  It is also used to show the grammatical agency of the noun governed by it, after a verb of wonder; or after a noun of excess importing love or hatred; [as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aHab~ahu A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"مَا اَحَبَّهُ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How lovely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing, is he to me!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hb","text_ar":"حب"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^abogaDahu A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"مَا اَبْغَضَهُ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How hateful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odious, is he to me!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bgD","text_ar":"بغض"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and] as in the saying [in the Kur xii. 33],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~i","text_ar":"رَبِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ijonu A^aHab~u A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"السِّجْنُ اَحَبُّ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my Lord, the prison is more pleasing to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee, K.) [This usage is similar to that explained in the next sentence.] ―         -b6-  It is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda","text_ar":"عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mughnee, Msb, K;) as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^a$ohaY A_ilaY~a mino ka*aA","text_ar":"هُوَ اَشْهَى اـِلَىَّ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is more desirable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant, in my estimation than such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) and in the saying of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^amo laA sabiyla A_ilaY Al$~abaAbi wa*ikoruhu\n                      \n                     \n                        A^a$ohaY A_ilaY~a mina Alr~aHiyqi Als~alosali"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is there no way"},{"kind":"text","text":"of return"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to youth, seeing that the remembrance thereof is more pleasant to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in my estimation, than mellow wine?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mughnee, K:) and accord. to this usage of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda","text_ar":"عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be explained the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoti","text_ar":"اَنْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN A_ilaY sanapK","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ اـِلَى سَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art divorced at"},{"kind":"text","text":"the commencement of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a year."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b7-  It is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn."},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"li","text_ar":"لِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlA^amoru A_ilayoka","text_ar":"وَالاَمْرُ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And command,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to command, belongeth unto Thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning God, as in the Kur xiii. 30, and xxx. 3], (Mughnee, K,) in a trad. respecting supplication: (TA:) or, as some say, it is here used in the manner first explained above, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is ultimately referrible to Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomadu","text_ar":"اَحْمَدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~`ha A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اللّٰهَ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I tell the praise of God unto thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mughnee:) [but see another rendering of this last phrase above:] you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka A_ilayoka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is committed to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thy arbitration."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 329.) ―         -b8-  It also occurs as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the saying in the Kur [xvii. 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaDayonaA A_ilaY","text_ar":"وَقَضَيْنَا اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniY A_isoraAy^iyla","text_ar":"بَنِى اـِسْرَايِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we decreed against the children of Israel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and we revealed to the children of Israel"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decisively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) ―         -b9-  It is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Mughnee, K;) as in the saying [in the Kur iv. 89 and vi.12],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layajomaEan~akumo A_ilaY yawomi AlqiyaAmapi","text_ar":"لَيَجْمَعَنَّكُمْ اـِلَى يَوْمِ القِيَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He will assuredly collect you together on the day of resurrection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) thus it may be used in this instance accord. to Ibn-Málik: (Mughnee:) and it is said to be so used in the saying [of En-Nábighah, (M, TA,)]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falaA tatorukan~iY biAlwaEiydi kaA^an~aniY\n                      \n                     \n                        A_ilay Aln~aAsi maToliY~N bihi AlqaAru A^ajorabu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then do not thou leave me with threatening, as though I were, among men, smeared with tar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being like a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mangy"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel]; (M, Mughnee;) or, accord. to some, there is an ellipsis and inversion in this verse;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY","text_ar":"الى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here in dependence upon a word suppressed, and the meaning being,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smeared with pitch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like a camel,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yet being united to men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to Ibn-'Osfoor,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mTlY~","text_ar":"مطلىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here considered as made to import the meaning of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered hateful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he says that if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY","text_ar":"الى"},{"kind":"text","text":"were correctly used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":", it it would be allowable to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodNA_ilaY Alkuwfapi","text_ar":"زَيْدٌاـِلَى الكُوفَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mughnee:) [or the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though I were, compared to men, a mangy"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smeared with pitch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] I'Ab said, after mentioning 'Alee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilomiY A_ilaY Eilomihi kaAlqaraArapi fiY AlmuvuEanojari","text_ar":"عِلْمِى اـِلَى عِلْمِهِ كَالقَرَارَةِ فِى المُثُعَنْجَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My knowledge compared to his knowledge is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrArp","text_ar":"قرارة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small pool of water left by a torrent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"placed by the side of the middle of the sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the main deep"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vEjr","text_ar":"ثعجر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It is also [said to be] used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the saying in the Kur [1xxix. 18],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo laka A_ilaY A^ano tazak~aY","text_ar":"هَلْ لَكَ اـِلَى اَنْ تَزَكَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wilt thou purify thyself"},{"kind":"text","text":"from infidelity?] because it imports the meaning of invitation. (TA.) ―         -b10-  It is also used [in a manner contr. to its primitive application, i. e.,] to denote beginning, [or origination,] being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the saying [of a poet],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taquwlu waqado EaAlayotu biAlkuwri fawoqahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        A^ayusoqay falaA yarowaY A_ilaY~a Abonu A^aHomaraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She says,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely my camel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when I have raised the saddle upon her, Will Ibn-Ahmar be supplied with drink and not satisfy his thirst from me?"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., will he never be satisfied with drawing forth my sweat?]. (Mughnee, K.) ―         -b11-  It is also used as a corroborative, and is thus [syntactically] redundant; as in the saying in the Kur [xiv. 40],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAjoEalo A^afoy^idapF mina Aln~aAsi tahowaY A_ilayohimo","text_ar":"فَاجْعَلْ اَفْيِدَةً مِنَ النَّاسِ تَهْوَى اـِلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"thwY","text_ar":"تهوى"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mughnee, K,) accord."},{"kind":"page_break","n":86},{"kind":"text","text":"to one reading, (Mughnee,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahowaAhumo","text_ar":"تَهْوَاهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And make Thou hearts of men to love them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) so says Fr: but some explain it by saying that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"thwY","text_ar":"تهوى"},{"kind":"text","text":"imports the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamiylu","text_ar":"تَمِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahowiY","text_ar":"تَهْوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, the kesreh being changed to a fet-hah, and the yé to an alif, as when one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDaA","text_ar":"رَضَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa","text_ar":"رَضِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASaApN","text_ar":"نَاصَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyapN","text_ar":"نَاصِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says Ibn-Málik; but this requires consideration; for it is a condition in such cases that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the original form must be movent. (Mughnee.) [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hwY","text_ar":"هوى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., [is elliptical, and] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, I complain unto Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"take Thou me unto Thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b13-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA minoka waA_ilayoka","text_ar":"اَنَا مِنْكَ وَاـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am of thee, and related to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b14-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai*ohabo A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اِذْهَبْ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Betake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apply, thyself to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupy thyself with, thine own affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K. *) And similar to this is the phrase used by El-Aashà,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA*ohabiY maA A_ilayoki","text_ar":"فَاذْهَبِى مَا اـِلَيْكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayokumo","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone is used in a similar manner, elliptically, or as an imperative verbal noun, and] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Betake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apply, yourselves to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupy yourselves with, your own affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai*ohabuwA A_ilayokumo","text_ar":"اِذْهَبُوا اـِلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and retire ye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withdraw ye, to a distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far away, from us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka Ean~iY","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ عَنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refrain, thou from me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remove, withdraw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retire, thou to a distance from me:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyk","text_ar":"اليك"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense is an imperative verbal noun. (Har p. 508.) Sb says, (M,) or Akh, (Har ubi suprà,) I heard an Arab of the desert, on its being said to him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", reply,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as though it were said to him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remove, withdraw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retire, thou to a distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and he replied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will remove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (M.) Aboo-Fir' own says, satirizing a Nabathæan woman of whom he asked for water to drink,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA Talabota AlmaA='i qaAlato layokaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When thou shalt demand water, she will say, Retire thou to a distance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, [by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lykA","text_ar":"ليكا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layoka","text_ar":"لَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with an adjunct alif for the sake of the rhyme,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the sense last explained above. (M.) ―         -b15-  One also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayoka ka*aA","text_ar":"اـِلَيْكَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.) ―         -b16-  When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is immediately followed by the interrogative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", both together are written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaAma","text_ar":"اـِلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To what? whither?"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"till,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until, what time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when?"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how long?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in like manner one writes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAma","text_ar":"عَلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY maA","text_ar":"عَلَى مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S * and K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aAma","text_ar":"حَتَّامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY","text_ar":"حَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY","text_ar":"حَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Msb","Bd","Jel","K","M","T"]},{"entry_id":"n1146","headword_ar":"اـِلَى","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilFY","text_ar":"اـِلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alw","text_ar":"الو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1147","headword_ar":"اـِلَى","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alFY","text_ar":"اَلًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) the latter said by Zekereeyà to be the most common, and the same is implied in the S, but MF says that this is not known, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilowN","text_ar":"اـِلْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alowN","text_ar":"اَلْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Es-Semeen, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalowN","text_ar":"دَلْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Es-Semeen, TA,) [belonging to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alw","text_ar":"الو"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iloYN","text_ar":"اـِلْىٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloYN","text_ar":"اَلْىٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uloyN","text_ar":"اُلْيٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Es-Sakháwee, Zekereeyà, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (the same,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaA","text_ar":"اـِلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring at the end of a verse, but it may be a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EahodFA","text_ar":"عَهْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A benefit, benefaction, favour, boon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=laA='N","text_ar":"ا=لَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, S, M, K, &c.) IAmb says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilFY","text_ar":"اـِلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alFY","text_ar":"اَلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"are originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wilFA","text_ar":"وِلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walFA","text_ar":"وَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n1133","headword_ar":"اَلىُّ","root":"Alw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who swears much; who utters many oaths:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, K:) mentioned in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY","text_ar":"الى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the present is its proper art. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","T","K"]},{"entry_id":"n1139","headword_ar":"اَلِىَ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^olaY","text_ar":"يَاْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alFY","text_ar":"اَلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, large in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uloyap","text_ar":"اُلْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S, K. *)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alayota","text_ar":"اَلَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alw","text_ar":"الو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n1140","headword_ar":"اَلْىٌ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilFY","text_ar":"اـِلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alayaAnN","text_ar":"اَلَيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1141","headword_ar":"اَلًى","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilFY","text_ar":"اـِلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alayaAnN","text_ar":"اَلَيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1142","headword_ar":"اُلْىٌّ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilFY","text_ar":"اـِلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1143","headword_ar":"اُلَى","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the S and in the M,) accord. to Sb, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulaA","text_ar":"اُلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so likewise in the M, in which it is mentioned in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY","text_ar":"الى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and thus it is always pronounced,]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaY","text_ar":"اُولَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (so in several copies of the S and in the K, in the last division of each of those works, [and thus it is generally written;]) and with the lengthened"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and this is the more common form of the word, i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulaA='i","text_ar":"اُلَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is always pronounced, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaA='i","text_ar":"اُولَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is generally written, both of which modes of writing it I find in the M.,] (S, M, K,) of the same measure as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAb","text_ar":"غُرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) indecl., with a kesreh for its termination; (S;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a pl. having no proper sing., (S, K,) or a noun denoting a pl., (M,) or its sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aA","text_ar":"ذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the masc. and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iho","text_ar":"ذِهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the fem., (S, K,) for it is both masc. and fem., (S,) and is applied to rational beings and to irrational things. (M.) [Thus,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^uwlaA='i EalaY A^avariY","text_ar":"هُمْ اُولَا=ءِ عَلَى اَثَرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xx. 86, means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are these, following near after me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are near me, coming near after me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel, and Bd says the like.) And in the same, iii. 115,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAA^anotumo A^uwlaA='i tuHib~uwnahumo walaA yuHib~uwnakumo","text_ar":"هَااَنْتُمْ اُولَا=ءِ تُحِبُّونَهُمْ وَلَا يُحِبُّونَكُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now ye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"O ye"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"these"},{"kind":"text","text":"believers,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"love them, and they love not you."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) ―         -b2-  The particle (M)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA","text_ar":"هَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) used as an inceptive to give notice of what is about to be said is prefixed to it, [i. e., to the form with the lengthened"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (S, M, K,) so that you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw^ulaA='i","text_ar":"هوُلَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h*aA","text_ar":"هذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means “this”]. (S, K.) And AZ says that some of the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw^alaA='i qawomuka","text_ar":"هوَلَا=ءِ قَوْمُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are thy people"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, M, *) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu hw^ulaA='K","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ هوُلَا=ءٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw these"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,) with tenween and kesr (S, M) to the hemzeh; (S;) and this, says IJ, is of the dial. of Benoo-'Okeyl. (M.) ―         -b3-  And the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"of allocution is added to it, so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwly^ika","text_ar":"اُوليِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=uwlaA=y^ika","text_ar":"ا=ُولَا=يِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the same, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwly^ikumo","text_ar":"اُوليِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaA=y^ikumo","text_ar":"اُولَا=يِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaAka","text_ar":"اُولَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaAlika","text_ar":"اُولَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the S and in the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulaAlika","text_ar":"اُلَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the S and in the M,) in which the [second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative, (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ul~aAka","text_ar":"اُلَّاكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with teshdeed, (K,) [all meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*lika","text_ar":"ذلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"mean “that” and hence] Ks says that when one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaA=y^ka","text_ar":"اُولَا=يكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*lika","text_ar":"ذلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and when one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaAka","text_ar":"اُولَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulaAlika","text_ar":"اُلَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaAlika","text_ar":"اُولَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", each with an augmentative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*lika","text_ar":"ذلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (and this, I doubt not, is the correct statement,)] is as though it were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*lika","text_ar":"ذلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) but one does not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAw^ulaAlika","text_ar":"هَاوُلَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hA^uwlaAlika","text_ar":"هاُولَالِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) [nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haw^ulaAy^ika","text_ar":"هَوُلَايِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the like.] [Thus it is said in the Kur ii. 4,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaA=y^ika Eala hudFY mino rab~ihimo waA^uwlaA=y^ika humu","text_ar":"اُولَا=يِكَ عَلَ هُدًى مِنْ رَبِّهِمْ وَاُولَا=يِكَ هُمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmufoliHuwna","text_ar":"المُفْلِحُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those follow a right direction from their Lord, and those are they who shall prosper."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaA=y^ika","text_ar":"اُولَا=يِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to irrational"},{"kind":"page_break","n":87},{"kind":"text","text":"things, as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEod A^uwlaA=y^ika AlA^ay~aAmi","text_ar":"بَعْد اُولَا=يِكَ الاَيَّامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"After those days"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in the Kur [xvii. 38], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Als~amoEa waAlobaSara waAlofuw^aAda kul~u A^uwlaA=y^ika","text_ar":"اـِنَّ السَّمْعَ وَالْبَصَرَ وَالْفُوَادَ كُلُّ اُولَا=يِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna Eanohu masow^uwlFA","text_ar":"كَانَ عَنْهُ مَسْوُولًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the ears and the eyes and the heart, all of those shall be inquired of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b4-  The dims. are ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ulay~aA","text_ar":"اـُلَيَّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ulay~aA='i","text_ar":"اُلَيَّا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw^ulay~aA='i","text_ar":"هوُلَيَّا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) for the formation of the dim. of a noun of vague application does not alter its commencement, but leaves it in its original state, with fet-h or damm, [as the case may be,] and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the characteristic of the dim. is inserted in the second place if the word is one of two letters, [as in the instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ay~aA","text_ar":"ذَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aA","text_ar":"ذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and in the third place if it is a word of three letters. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ulaY","text_ar":"الاُلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the S and T,) of the same measure as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEulaY","text_ar":"العُلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S; [wherefore the author of the TA prefers this mode of writing it, which expresses the manner in which it is always pronounced;]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ulaA","text_ar":"الاُلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISd, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^uwlaY","text_ar":"الاُولَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (so in some copies of the S and T;) is likewise a pl. having no proper sing., [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They who, those which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] its sing. being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY","text_ar":"الَّذِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or is changed from being a noun of indication so as to have the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iyna","text_ar":"الَّذِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ulaA='i","text_ar":"الاُلَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; wherefore they have the lengthened as well as the shortened alif, and that with the lengthened alif is made indecl. by terminating with a kesreh. (ISd.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA_in~a AlA_uwlaY biAlT~af~i mino A=li haA$imK\n                      \n                     \n                        taA=sawoA fasan~uwA lilokiraAmi Alt~aA=siyaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they who are in Et-Taff, of the family of Háshim, shared their property, one with another, and so set the example, to the generous, of the sharing of property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, and S in art."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n1145","headword_ar":"اـِلْىٌ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilFY","text_ar":"اـِلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1154","headword_ar":"اَلِىُ","root":"AlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned in this art. in the K: see art."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}